Part 4: Sharding, Clustering, and Nodes 

    • Sharding in MongoDB : Method to distribute large amount of data accross multiple servers. Each server stores a portion of data, called a shard.It helps MongoDB to handle large databases and improves performance.
    • Replica Set : A group of MongoDB servers that maintain the same data copies. It provides data redundancy and high availability
    • Primary node and Secondary nodes : A replica usually contains one Primary node and multiple Seconday nodes. If the primary fails, one secondary automatically becomes primary. It prevents data loss, and ensures better availability.
      Primary node recieves all write operations such as insert, update, delete.
      Secondary node copy data from the primary. They usually handle read operations and provide backup support.

